attributes.Long form description:
The instructor instructs you to begin setting up the table. The student approaches the table, separates the pieces of furniture, picks up and inspects the legs of the table. The instructor gives instructions on how to correctly position the table legs. The student aligns the legs, picks up the first screw and inspects it, picks up the Allen wrench from the table, begins to tighten the screws, turns the pieces slightly to tighten the next screw, picks up the next table leg, picks up the next screw and tightens it, picks up the next screw, drops the Allen wrench and picks it up, continues with the screws. After finish tightening the legs of the table with the middle tray of the cabinet, turns the cabinet over (stand it upright), takes the upper leg of the table, places it on the legs, removes the tray, places it on the table, turns the cabinet over the tray, aligns it, takes the screws and starts inserting them, tighten them one by one, turning the cabinet over (stand it upright). 
The instructor asks him to finish the recording.
